fields.body:
The following {{ log_level|lower }} message was logged:

{{ log_message }}
fields.subject: {{ log_level|upper }} Message Logged by Precor Experience VoD
{% autoescape off %}Welcome to Precor Experience{% endautoescape %}
{% autoescape off %}Congratulations and welcome to Precor Experience{% endautoescape %}
{% autoescape off %}password reset for Precor Experience{% endautoescape %}

fields.description: Returns True if the actor and the actee are both enrolled in the same session, for which actor is in the session_user_role actor_eur, and actee is in the session_user_role actee_eur.  Returns False otherwise.  This method is only for use when the actee is a user.
fields.title: Actor and actee are enrolled in the same session
fields.name: actor_actee_enrolled_in_same_session

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is an authenticated user who is acting upon themselves.  Only affects permissions for the user object
fields.title: Actor is acting upon themselves
fields.name: actor_is_acting_upon_themselves

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is an authenticated user
fields.title: Actor is authenticated
fields.name: actor_is_authenticated

fields.description: Returns True iff the Assignment's prerequisites have been met
fields.title: Assignment prerequisites have been met
fields.name: assignment_prerequisites_met

fields.description: Returns True iff the AssignmentAttempt's start date is after the Assignment's effective_date_assigned
fields.title: AssignmentAttempt meets date restrictions
fields.name: assignment_attempt_meets_date_restrictions

fields.description: Returns True iff the AssignmentAttempt's prerequisites have been met
fields.title: AssignmentAttempt prerequisites have been met
fields.name: assignment_attempt_prerequisites_met

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is the manager of the group they are acting upon
fields.title: Actor is the manager of the group in question
fields.name: actor_is_group_manager

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is a member of the group they are acting upon
fields.title: Actor is a user in the group in question
fields.name: actor_is_in_actee_which_is_a_group

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is a guest, which means they have not authenticated or logged in
fields.title: Actor is a guest
fields.name: actor_is_guest

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is an instructor manager for a product line for which the actee is listed as an instructor
fields.title: Actor is the instructor manager of the actee
fields.name: actor_is_instructor_manager_of_actee

fields.description: Returns true if the actor is a member of the specified group. Specify a group by passing its ID as 'group_id'
fields.title: Actor is Member of Group
fields.name: actor_member_of_group

fields.description: Returns True if the actor owns the address in question.  Only affects permissions on the address object
fields.title: Actor owns the address
fields.name: actor_owns_address

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is the product line manager for the product line being accessed.
fields.title: Actor is product line manager for a given product line
fields.name: actor_is_product_line_manager_of_product_line

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is the product line manager for the product line of the session being accessed.
fields.title: Actor is product line manager for the session_template being accessed
fields.name: actor_is_product_line_manager_of_session

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is the product line manager for the product line of the session_template being accessed.
fields.title: Actor is product line manager for the session being accessed
fields.name: actor_is_product_line_manager_of_session_template

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is the product line manager for the product line of the user being accessed.
fields.title: Actor is product line manager for the user being accessed
fields.name: actor_is_product_line_manager_of_user

fields.description: Returns True if the actor owns the purchase order being accessed.
fields.title: Actor is the owner of the purchase order being accessed
fields.name: actor_owns_purchase_order

fields.description: Returns True if the purchase order being accessed has at least one payment.
fields.title: Purchase Order being accessed has payments
fields.name: purchase_order_has_payments

fields.description: Returns True if the purchase order being accessed has no payments.
fields.title: Purchase Order being accessed has no payments
fields.name: purchase_order_has_no_payments

fields.description: Returns True if the actor owns the training_unit_authorization being accessed.
fields.title: Actor owns the training_unit_authorization being accessed
fields.name: actor_owns_training_unit_authorization

fields.description: Returns True if the actor owns the purchase order against which the currently accessed payment was made,
fields.title: Actor owns the given payment
fields.name: actor_owns_payment

fields.description: Returns true if the refund does not put the total amount of refunds for a particular payment over the value of the payment
fields.title: Refund does not exceed payment
fields.name: refund_does_not_exceed_payment

fields.description: Returns true if the assignment is for a session at a venue that matches the actor's preferred venue
fields.title: Assignment venue matches actor venue
fields.name: assignment_venue_matches_actor_preferred_venue

fields.description: Returns true if the actor is of the specified status.
fields.title: Actor is of specified status
fields.name: actor_status_check

fields.description: Always returns True.
fields.title: Actor is any user
fields.name: actor_is_anybody

fields.description: This is a strange new breed of auth_check that concerns itself with the update_dict.  It ensures that the update_dict is only attempting to add items from the list of allowed primary keys to the attribute on the actee.  It will return false if any 'remove' operation is in the dict, or if any primary key appears in the add list that is not in the allowed primary key list.
fields.title: Actor is adding allowed many ended objects to user
fields.name: actor_is_adding_allowed_many_ended_objects_to_user

fields.description: Returns True if the actor owns the event.
fields.title: Actor owns the event
fields.name: actor_owns_event

fields.description: Returns True if the actor owns the session.
fields.title: Actor owns the session
fields.name: actor_owns_session

fields.description: Returns True if the actor owns the session_user_role_requirement.
fields.title: Actor owns the session_user_role_requirement
fields.name: actor_owns_session_user_role_requirement

fields.description: Does nothing if the exam_session has no answered questions or ratings.  Returns True if exam_session is finished, else False.
fields.title: Populated exam_session is finished.
fields.name: populated_exam_session_is_finished

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is the user who created the venue, which is discovered by examining the venue's blame
fields.title: The actor is the venue's creator
fields.name: actor_is_venue_creator

fields.description: Returns True iff the session_user_role associate with the actee is the same as the session_user_role specified by the parameter session_user_role.
fields.title: session_user_role_requirement is of a particular session_user_role
fields.name: surr_is_of_a_particular_sur

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor is the owner of the credential
fields.title: Actor owns Credential
fields.name: actor_owns_credential

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor has completed all of the prerequisite tasks for the task being queried.
fields.title: Actor has completed Task prerequisites
fields.name: actor_has_completed_task_prerequisites

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor is the owner of the AchievementAward
fields.title: Actor owns AchievementAward
fields.name: actor_owns_achievement_award

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor is the owner of an AchievementAward for the Achievement
fields.title: Actor owns AchievementAward for Achievement
fields.name: actor_owns_achievement_award_for_achievement

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor is the owner of the assignment
fields.title: Actor owns Assignment
fields.name: actor_owns_assignment

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor is the owner of the assignment attempt
fields.title: Actor owns AssignmentAttempt
fields.name: actor_owns_assignment_attempt

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor has completed all of the prerequisite Tasks for the Assignment being queried.
fields.title: Actor has completed Assignment prerequisites
fields.name: actor_has_completed_assignment_prerequisites

fields.description: Returns True iff the QuestionResponse is for an ExamSession owned by the actor.
fields.title: Actor owns QuestionResponse
fields.name: actor_owns_question_response

fields.description: This complicatedly name method exists to be a bit genericly useful.  It will examine actee, ensuring that it is of type actee_model_name.  It will then ensure that attribute_name's value is equal to attribute_value.
fields.title: Actee's attribute is set to
fields.name: actees_attribute_is_set_to

fields.description: This complicatedly name method exists to be a bit genericly useful.  It will examine actee, ensuring that it is of type actee_model_name.  It will then follow a foreign key relationship, actee.foreign_object_attribute_name, and ensure that that attribute's value is equal to foreign_object_attribute_value.
fields.title: Actee's foreign key object has attribute set to
fields.name: actees_foreign_key_object_has_attribute_set_to

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is the owner of the Assignment, or if the actor is a guest and the Assignment doesn't have a user defined.
fields.title: Actor owns assignment or is guest
fields.name: actor_owns_assignment_or_is_guest

fields.description: Returns True if the actor is the same User object as is listed in the OwnedPRModel's owner field.
fields.title: Actor owns PRModel
fields.name: actor_owns_prmodel

fields.description: If the actee is in the group, the method returns True iff they are also of the domain.  If they are not in the group, it will return True.  This is useful for making sure that participants who register themselves are in the constantcontact.com domain.
fields.title: Actee is in group and domain
fields.name: actee_is_in_group_and_domain

fields.description: Returns True if DomainAffiliation.user is the actor.
fields.title: DomainAffiliation user is actor
fields.name: actor_related_to_domain_affiliation

fields.description: Returns True if the actee is an Organization and the actor belongs to that organization
fields.title: Actor is in actee organization
fields.name: actor_is_in_actee_which_is_an_organization

fields.description: Returns True iff the actee is an Assignment the Task in which is not a Video
fields.title: Assignment is not to watch Video
fields.name: assignment_is_not_video

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor is a manager of a category that the actee is directly or indirectly related to, and the relationship is not through a deleted video
fields.title: Actor is Category Manager of category related to actee
fields.name: actor_is_manager_of_actee_related_category

fields.description: Returns true iff the actor is a member of an authorized group on a category that's in an approved relationship to the actee
fields.title: Actor is a member of an actee-related Category's authorized groups
fields.name: actor_is_member_of_actee_related_category_authorized_groups

fields.description: Returns true iff the actor is a member of any Organization
fields.title: Actor is member of any Organization
fields.name: actor_is_member_of_any_organization

fields.description: Returns True iff actor owns an assignment for the given task
fields.title: Actor owns Assignment for Task
fields.name: actor_owns_assignment_for_task

fields.description: Returns True iff the actor has an assignment for this session
fields.title: Actor is assigned to the session
fields.name: actor_assigned_to_session
